<i>noun</i>: 중수 [중ː수], 정비 [정ː비], 쇄신 [쇄ː신], 개조 [개ː조], 개신 [개ː신], 개변 [개ː변] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>중수 [중ː수]</dt><br>
<dd>renovation</dd><br>
<dd>오래된 건물의 낡고 헌 부분을 손질하여 고침.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of tending to and fixing the old, worn-out parts of an age-old building.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>정비 [정ː비]</dt><br>
<dd>1. overhaul</dd><br>
<dd>흐트러진 체계를 정리하여 제대로 갖춤.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of renovating a flawed system to make it work.</dd><br>
<dd>2. maintenance; repair</dd><br>
<dd>기계나 설비가 제대로 작동하도록 보살피고 손질함.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of taking care of and repairing machinery or equipment to make it function properly.</dd><br>
<dd>3. renovation; repair</dd><br>
<dd>도로나 시설이 제 기능을 하도록 정리함.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of fixing roads or facilities to make them serve their purpose.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>쇄신 [쇄ː신]</dt><br>
<dd>reform; renovation</dd><br>
<dd>나쁜 관습이나 낡은 사상 등을 버리고 새롭게 함.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of throwing away bad customs, old ideas, etc., and making new ones.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>개조 [개ː조]</dt><br>
<dd>remodeling; renovation</dd><br>
<dd>고쳐 새롭게 만들거나 바꿈.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of fixing or remaking something.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>개신 [개ː신]</dt><br>
<dd>renewal; renovation</dd><br>
<dd>시대에 뒤떨어진 제도, 관습 등을 새롭게 고침.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of updating anachronistic policies or customs.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>개변 [개ː변]</dt><br>
<dd>innovation; reformation; renovation</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 상태, 제도, 시설 등을 더 좋게 만들려고 고치거나 바꾸는 것.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of changing or altering to make better certain situations, systems and facilities.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>